Vitamin A.why: A lack of vitamin A can lead to impaired skin cell turnover, causing dead skin cells to clog pores and lead to acne.
Vitamin A.tip: Include vitamin A-rich foods in your breakfast to boost skin health throughout the day.

Zinc.why: A lack of zinc can disrupt the balance of hormones, leading to increased sebum production and clogged pores, which can cause acne.
Zinc.tip: Take a zinc supplement or consume zinc-rich foods with acidic meals to enhance absorption.

Omega-3 fatty acids.why: A lack of omega-3 fatty acids can lead to inflammation in the body, which can exacerbate acne by increasing redness and swelling.
Omega-3 fatty acids.tip: Incorporate omega-3 rich foods into your diet 2-3 times a week to reduce inflammation.
